<p>Tabs can be nested within tabs, but the most obvious method (putting a [[tabview]] within another [[tabview]]) will not work. There is a specific method required for nesting tabs, but I don't recommend doing it due to readability issues. Just make another sandbox page at that point.</p>
<h1 id="toc9"><span>Tables</span></h1>
<p>Tables can be useful for experiment logs, or SCPs with a large number of component entities:</p>
<blockquote>
<p><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">||~&#32;TITLE-FORMATTED&#32;CELL&#32;||~&#32;TITLE-FORMATTED&#32;CELL&#32;||~&#32;TITLE-FORMATTED&#32;CELL&#32;||</span><br />
<span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">||&#32;Non-formatted&#32;cell&#32;||&#32;Non-formatted&#32;cell&#32;||&#32;Non-formatted&#32;cell&#32;||</span><br />
<span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">||&lt;&#32;Left-aligned&#32;cell&#32;||&lt;&#32;Left-aligned&#32;cell&#32;||&lt;&#32;Left-aligned&#32;cell&#32;||</span><br />
<span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">||&gt;&#32;Right-aligned&#32;cell&#32;||&gt;&#32;Right-aligned&#32;cell&#32;||&gt;&#32;Right-aligned&#32;cell&#32;||</span><br />
<span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">||=&#32;Center-aligned&#32;cell&#32;||=&#32;Center-aligned&#32;cell&#32;||=&#32;Center-aligned&#32;cell||</span></p>
</blockquote>
<table class="wiki-content-table">
<tr>
<th>TITLE-FORMATTED CELL</th>
<th>TITLE-FORMATTED CELL</th>
<th>TITLE-FORMATTED CELL</th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Non-formatted cell</td>
<td>Non-formatted cell</td>
<td>Non-formatted cell</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td style="text-align: left;">Left-aligned cell</td>
<td style="text-align: left;">Left-aligned cell</td>
<td style="text-align: left;">Left-aligned cell</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td style="text-align: right;">Right-aligned cell</td>
<td style="text-align: right;">Right-aligned cell</td>
<td style="text-align: right;">Right-aligned cell</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td style="text-align: center;">Center-aligned cell</td>
