<td style="text-align: center;">Center-aligned cell</td>
</tr>
</table>
<p>Adding more cell separators (||) before the cell's text will make the cell span multiple columns based on how many cell separators you used:</p>
<blockquote>
<p><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">||~&#32;Cell&#32;title&#32;||~&#32;Cell&#32;title&#32;||~&#32;Cell&#32;title&#32;||</span><br />
<span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">||&#32;Cell&#32;spanning&#32;one&#32;column&#32;||||&#32;Cell&#32;spanning&#32;two&#32;columns&#32;||</span><br />
<span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">||||||&#32;Cell&#32;spanning&#32;three&#32;columns||</span></p>
</blockquote>
